<inglise> This Directive shall apply to food additives the various categories of which are given in Annex I and which are used or intended to be used as ingredients during the manufacture or preparation of a foodstuff and are still present in the final product, even if in altered form, hereinafter called 'food additives'. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse I lisas loetletud mitmesugustesse r&uuml;hmadesse kuuluvate lisaainete suhtes, mida kasutatakse v&otilde;i mis on ette n&auml;htud toiduaine tootmisel v&otilde;i valmistamisel tarvitatavate koostisainetena ja mis samal v&otilde;i muudetud kujul on olemas ka l&otilde;pptootes; edaspidi "lisaained". </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive 'food additive' means any substance not normally consumed as a food in itself and not normally used as a characteristic ingredient of food whether or not it has nutritive value, the intentional addition of which to food for a technological purpose in the manufacture, processing, preparation, treatment, packaging, transport or storage of such food results, or may be reasonably expected to result, in it or its by-products becoming directly or indirectly a component of such foods. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis on "lisaaine" aine, mida olenemata tema toitev&auml;&auml;rtusest ei kasutata iseseisva toiduainena v&otilde;i toiduainele iseloomuliku koostisainena ja mille tahtlik tehnoloogilisel eesm&auml;rgil lisamine toiduainele selle tootmisel, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel, valmistamisel, k&auml;itlemisel, pakendamisel, transpordil v&otilde;i ladustamisel viib v&otilde;i v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjendatud oletusel viia selleni, et lisaaine ise v&otilde;i tema k&otilde;rvalsaadused muutuvad otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt selliste toiduainete koostisosaks. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
