<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Food additives can be approved only provided that: </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaained v&otilde;idakse heaks kiita ainult siis, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> - there can be demonstrated a reasonable technological need and the purpose cannot be achieved by other means which are economically and technologically Practicable, </inglise>
<eesti> - suudetakse &auml;ra n&auml;idata m&otilde;istlik tehnoloogiline vajadus ja asjaolu, et eesm&auml;rki ei ole v&otilde;imalik saavutada &uuml;helgi teisel majanduslikult ja tehnoloogiliselt teostataval viisil, </eesti>
<inglise> - they present no hazard to the health of the consumer at the level of use proposed, so far as can be judged on the scientific evidence available, </inglise>
<eesti> - soovitatud kasutustaseme puhul ei ole nad tarbija tervisele ohtlikud, niipalju kui seda saab otsustada k&auml;ttesaadava teadusliku t&otilde;endusmaterjali p&otilde;hjal, </eesti>
<inglise> - they do not mislead the consumer. </inglise>
<eesti> - nende kasutamine ei eksita tarbijat. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The use of food additives may be considered only where there is evidence that the proposed use of the additive would have demonstrable advantages of benefit to the consumer, in other words it is necessary to establish the case for what is commonly referred to as 'need'. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaainete kasutamist v&otilde;idakse kaaluda ainult siis, kui on ilmne, et tarbija saab sellest t&otilde;estatavat tulu; teiste s&otilde;nadega, on vaja kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata, mida t&auml;hendab &uuml;ldiselt kasutatav m&otilde;iste "vajadus". </eesti>
<inglise> The use of food additives should serve one or more of the purposes set out from points (a) to (d) and only where these purposes cannot be achieved by other means which are economically and technologically practicable and do not present a hazard to the health of the consumer: </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaaineid tuleks kasutada &uuml;hel v&otilde;i mitmel punktides a - d s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rgil ja ainult sel juhul, kui neid eesm&auml;rke ei ole v&otilde;imalik saavutada muul majanduslikult ja tehnoloogiliselt teostataval ning tarbija tervisele ohutul viisil: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) to preserve the nutritional quality of the food: an intentional reduction in the nutritional quality of a food would be justified only where the food does not constitute a significant item in a normal diet or where the additive is necessary for the production of foods for groups of consumers having special dietary needs; </inglise>
<eesti> a) toiduainete toitev&auml;&auml;rtuse s&auml;ilitamine; toiduaine toitev&auml;&auml;rtuse tahtlik v&auml;hendamine oleks &otilde;igustatud ainult siis, kui sel toiduainel ei ole tavalises toiduvalikus suurt t&auml;htsust v&otilde;i kui lisaainet on vaja toiduainete tootmiseks eritoitu vajavatele tarbijar&uuml;hmadele; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) to provide necessary ingredients or constituents for foods manufactured for groups of consumers having special dietary needs; </inglise>
<eesti> b) eritoitu vajavatele tarbijar&uuml;hmadele toiduainete vajalike koostisainete v&otilde;i koostisosade tootmine; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) to enhance the keeping quality or stability of a food or to improve its organoleptic properties, provided that this does not so change the nature, substance or quality of the food as to deceive the consumer; </inglise>
<eesti> c) toiduaine s&auml;ilivuse v&otilde;i stabiilsuse, samuti tema organoleptiliste omaduste parandamine, kui see ei muuda toiduaine laadi, olemust v&otilde;i kvaliteeti ega eksita tarbijat; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) to provide aids in manufacture, processing, preparation, treatment, packing, transport or storage of food, provided that the additive is not used to disguise the effects of the use of faulty raw materials or of undesirable (including unhygienic) practices or techniques during the course of any of these activities. </inglise>
<eesti> d) toiduainete tootmise, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise, valmistamise, k&auml;itlemise, pakendamise, transpordi v&otilde;i ladustamise lihtsustamine tingimusel, et lisaainet ei kasutata selleks, et varjata kasutatud v&auml;hese v&auml;&auml;rtusega toorainete m&otilde;ju v&otilde;i nimetatud toimingute ajal kasutatavaid ebasoovitavaid (sealhulgas ebah&uuml;gieenilisi) toiminguid. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> To assess the possible harmful effects of a food additive or derivatives thereof, it must be subjected to appropriate toxicological testing and evaluation. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaaine v&otilde;i selle derivaatide v&otilde;imalike kahjulike toimete kindlakstegemiseks tuleb korraldada n&otilde;uetekohane toksilisuse kontroll ja hindamine. </eesti>
<inglise> The evaluation should also take into account, for example, any cumulative, synergistic or potentiating effect of its use and the phenomenon of human intolerance to substances foreign to the body. </inglise>
<eesti> Hindamisel tuleb n&auml;iteks arvesse v&otilde;tta lisaaine kasutamise k&otilde;iki kumulatiivseid, s&uuml;nergilisi v&otilde;i soodustavaid m&otilde;jusid ning inimese taluvust kehav&otilde;&otilde;raste ainete suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> All food additives must be kept under continuous observation and must be re-evaluated whenever necessary in the light of changing conditions of use and new scientific information. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;iki lisaaineid tuleb hoida pideva vaatluse all ja vajaduse korral seoses muutuvate kasutustingimuste ja uue teadusinfoga uuesti hinnata. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Food additives must at all times comply with the approved criteria of purity. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaained peavad alati vastama heakskiidetud puhtusekriteeriumidele. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> Approval for food additives must: </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaainete heakskiitmisel tuleb: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) specify the foodstuffs to which these additives may be added and the conditions under which they may be added; </inglise>
<eesti> a) kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata toiduained, millele neid lisaaineid v&otilde;ib lisada, ja lisaainete lisamise tingimused; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) be limited to the lowest level of use necessary to achieve the desired effect; </inglise>
<eesti> b) piirata lisaainete kasutamist soovitava m&otilde;ju saavutamiseks vajaliku madalaima tasemeni; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) take into account any acceptable daily intake, or equivalent assessment, established for the food additive and the probable daily intake of it from all sources. </inglise>
<eesti> c) arvestada lisaainele kehtestatud vastuv&otilde;etavat p&auml;evast kogust v&otilde;i muud samav&auml;&auml;rset kriteeriumi ning k&otilde;ikidest allikatest saadavat oletatavat lisaaine p&auml;evast kogust. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the food additive is to be used in foods eaten by special groups of consumers, account should be taken of the possible daily intake of the food additive by consumers in those groups. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui lisaainet kasutatakse toiduainetes, mis on ette n&auml;htud eri tarbijar&uuml;hmadele, tuleks arvestada neisse r&uuml;hmadesse kuuluvate tarbijate v&otilde;imalikku p&auml;evast lisaaine kogust. </eesti>
 